17/02/2004
VIENNA, Austria -- Foreign Minister Benita Ferrero-Waldner met with Croatian counterpart Miomir Zuzul on Monday (16 February) and pledged her country's strong support for Croatia's efforts to join the EU. She said she hopes Zagreb could catch up to Bulgaria and Romania and join the Union in 2007.
In other news, a Croatian working at his country's embassy in the Netherlands has been arrested. The employee, identified as Bozidar Loncarek, was allegedly carrying 1 kg of cocaine in a diplomatic courier pouch at The Hague. (Vjesnik, HRT, HINA - 16/02/04)
